HmActionValue.name: HmActionValue
HmActionValue.description: Trigger a action on the device. Reading the variable normally returns noop. The processing state and the termination result can be monitored with SNMP Protocol Extension MIB.

HmTimeHHMM24.name: HmTimeHHMM24
HmTimeHHMM24.description: The time in hh:mm format: range for hh: 0 to 23 range for mm: 0 to 59

HmLargeDisplayString.name: HmLargeDisplayString
HmLargeDisplayString.description: Represents textual information taken from the NVT ASCII character set, as defined in pages 4, 10-11 of RFC 854. To summarize RFC 854, the NVT ASCII repertoire specifies: - the use of character codes 0-127 (decimal) - the graphics characters (32-126) are interpreted as US ASCII - NUL, LF, CR, BEL, BS, HT, VT and FF have the special meanings specified in RFC 854 - the other 25 codes have no standard interpretation - the sequence 'CR LF' means newline - the sequence 'CR NUL' means carriage-return - an 'LF' not preceded by a 'CR' means moving to the same column on the next line. - the sequence 'CR x' for any x other than LF or NUL is illegal. (Note that this also means that a string may end with either 'CR LF' or 'CR NUL', but not with CR.) Any object defined using this syntax may not exceed 2048 characters in length.
